If the port is not present this will return undefined. I don't know if that would be an issue on the backend or not. I would expect to pass an empty string.

This function is for showing the data on the table, and when either port or IP address is undefined it is displayed as blank on the frontend. Also, while adding the destination, data is sent to backend and that is done using addDestination action.
Create a string which will hold 'smtp' value and then add the remaining strings at the last, avoid repetition of code.

For subscriptions.Destination , subscriptions.Destination.split('/')[2].split(':') and subscriptions.Destination.split(':') create variable using destructuring and then use it.

Please don't hardcode routes like this.  Not all systems will support EventService.  Every place we do this incorrectly makes it one more page that we will need to rework in the future.


https://github.com/openbmc/webui-vue/issues/43

I suspect once this is unhardcoded, the configuration option for this page will be unnecessary, as it can just key off the existence of the EventService route.

> I suspect once this is unhardcoded, the configuration option for this page will be unnecessary, as it can just key off the existence of the EventService route. 

We should change this to get the oData link for EventService and make a call and get the oData link for Subscriptions and then map the data. This will solve one issue, but we still have navigation challenges to handle. We also are hard coding navigation (vue router) and it is likely that we would need to manage the vue routes dynamically also based on the availability of Redfish properties. The way we are accomodating that currently is by creating custom routing to exclude or include routes and navigation.

I am not quite sure what is meant by the configuration option for this page. I apologize if it's obvious and I am just missing it.
I think we can remove this. 😊

With that said, once again, this is better than what's already here in other handlers.
